{\an8}FAT TONY:

228
00:09:36,367 --> 00:09:38,037
{\an8}BOTH:

229
00:09:38,119 --> 00:09:39,749
<i>NARRATOR:</i>
<i>And at his next game,</i>

230
00:09:39,829 --> 00:09:42,119
<i>Bart did a very odd thing.</i>

231
00:09:42,206 --> 00:09:44,666
DREDERICK TATUM: And with Springfield
up by a meager one point,

232
00:09:44,750 --> 00:09:45,920
star guard Bart Simpson

233
00:09:46,002 --> 00:09:47,552
is just dribbling,
he's not shooting,

234
00:09:47,628 --> 00:09:48,748
with two minutes to go.

235
00:09:48,838 --> 00:09:50,968
♪ ♪

236
00:09:56,178 --> 00:09:58,718
{\an8}I don't know how,
but Homer gained 12 pounds

237
00:09:58,806 --> 00:10:00,266
{\an8}chewing towels.

238
00:10:00,349 --> 00:10:02,519
I put jelly on 'em.

239
00:10:02,602 --> 00:10:03,812
(whistle blows)

240
00:10:03,894 --> 00:10:06,194
Time expired!

241
00:10:06,272 --> 00:10:08,942
Bart didn't know it,
but he was point shaving.

242
00:10:09,025 --> 00:10:10,735
That's when a player
wins the game,

243
00:10:10,818 --> 00:10:13,358
{\an8}but makes sure his team
doesn't cover the spread.

244
00:10:13,446 --> 00:10:16,736
The team's happy, the gamblers
are happy, everybody wins.

245
00:10:16,824 --> 00:10:18,784
The only unhappy person
is someone like me,

246
00:10:18,868 --> 00:10:20,618
who has to explain the thing.

247
00:10:20,703 --> 00:10:23,463
Well, at least you'll let me
play my saxophone.

248
00:10:23,539 --> 00:10:24,709
(inhales deeply)

249
00:10:24,790 --> 00:10:26,250
Good thing you cut that song.

250
00:10:26,334 --> 00:10:30,094
Did you know I once took a train
halfway across Cleveland?

251
00:10:30,171 --> 00:10:32,091
<i>NARRATOR:</i>
<i>This is not a video trick.</i>

252
00:10:32,173 --> 00:10:33,803
<i>He really just stopped moving,</i>

253
00:10:33,883 --> 00:10:36,433
<i>but Bart had just gotten started.</i>

254
00:10:36,510 --> 00:10:37,850
♪ ♪

255
00:10:52,652 --> 00:10:55,742
You could be an accessory
to a crime, you know.

256
00:10:55,821 --> 00:10:57,571
Are you letting
your anger at Dad

257
00:10:57,657 --> 00:11:00,157
make you into
a patsy for the mob?

258
00:11:00,242 --> 00:11:02,082
Hey, Bart Simpson
is nobody's patsy.

259
00:11:02,161 --> 00:11:06,041
Hey, Bart, Fat Tony says to win
by less than six points.

260
00:11:06,123 --> 00:11:08,793
Here's a list of acceptable
point differentials.

261
00:11:08,876 --> 00:11:10,836
It could be five, four, three...

262
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:13,050
You realize you're
having this conversation

263
00:11:13,130 --> 00:11:14,300
in front of a reporter.

264
00:11:14,382 --> 00:11:15,882
Hey, I don't see no reporter.

265
00:11:15,966 --> 00:11:18,716
I see a little girl with
futile dreams of fitting in.

266
00:11:18,803 --> 00:11:21,813
Gee whiz, you don't
have to be so mean.

267
00:11:21,889 --> 00:11:24,559
That's the business I'm in!
Whoa! Hey!

268
00:11:27,228 --> 00:11:29,188
(calliope music playing)

269
00:11:36,654 --> 00:11:39,414
Shoot! Shoot!
Just like I drew it up!

270
00:11:39,490 --> 00:11:40,990
Okay, here's a shot:

271
00:11:41,075 --> 00:11:44,075
you're not bald, your hair left
out of embarrassment.

272
00:11:44,161 --> 00:11:46,081
-Why, you little...!
-(choking)

273
00:11:46,163 --> 00:11:47,503
(crowd gasps)

274
00:11:47,581 --> 00:11:48,421
(crowd cheers)

275
00:11:48,499 --> 00:11:50,329
(buzzer blares)

276
00:11:50,418 --> 00:11:53,248
I'll teach you
to win the game!

277
00:11:53,337 --> 00:11:55,257
You stupid buzzer-beating,
clutch-shooting...

278
00:11:55,339 --> 00:11:56,509
Oh, come on, man.

279
00:11:56,590 --> 00:11:58,510
-...ice water in your veins...
-I'm taking my talents to Shelbyville.

280
00:11:58,592 --> 00:12:00,512
...here comes
the post-game interview!

281
00:12:00,594 --> 00:12:02,644
This is the first thing you've done
as a coach.

282
00:12:02,722 --> 00:12:04,772
You have to give them credit!
They played hard!

283
00:12:04,849 --> 00:12:06,809
-People are gonna hear about this, Dad.
-I'm so proud of these boys,

284
00:12:06,892 --> 00:12:09,602
-and especially our sixth man...
-You're still nicer than Bobby Knight.

285
00:12:09,687 --> 00:12:10,807
...the fans!

286
00:12:10,896 --> 00:12:12,856
All right, let me hear your side.

287
00:12:12,940 --> 00:12:15,360
Sorry, my side
is exclusive to my charity,

288
00:12:15,443 --> 00:12:17,073
The American Fart Association.

289
00:12:17,153 --> 00:12:17,993
Why, you little...!

290
00:12:18,070 --> 00:12:19,660
(grunting)

291
00:12:21,532 --> 00:12:24,242
(laughing)

292
00:12:24,326 --> 00:12:25,786
Checkmate.

293
00:12:25,870 --> 00:12:27,330
(laughs)

294
00:12:27,413 --> 00:12:28,913
D'oh!

295
00:12:28,998 --> 00:12:31,788
<i>NARRATOR: But the boy who could</i>
<i>spin a ball with his doodle</i>

296
00:12:31,876 --> 00:12:33,996
<i>was about to learn</i>
<i>a very tough lesson.</i>

297
00:12:37,506 --> 00:12:39,336
{\an8}BART:

298
00:12:39,425 --> 00:12:41,425
{\an8}FAT TONY:

299
00:12:43,763 --> 00:12:45,143
{\an8}BART:

300
00:12:45,222 --> 00:12:48,232
<i>NARRATOR: Fat Tony denied</i>
<i>he'd made any money,</i>

301
00:12:48,309 --> 00:12:52,059
<i>but this FBI footage</i>
<i>suggests otherwise.</i>

302
00:12:52,146 --> 00:12:54,056
I thought I was just
keeping the score down

303
00:12:54,148 --> 00:12:55,228
to get back at my Dad,

304
00:12:55,316 --> 00:12:57,986
but Fat Tony was betting
against us, every game.

305
00:12:58,068 --> 00:12:59,698
I was a patsy.

306
00:12:59,779 --> 00:13:01,239
Ow! She didn't mean that.

307
00:13:01,322 --> 00:13:03,822
D'oh! Ow! Ow!

308
00:13:11,832 --> 00:13:14,342
I was scared. Milhouse scared.

309
00:13:14,418 --> 00:13:17,168
Why do you keep cutting to me?

310
00:13:17,254 --> 00:13:19,014
And then it got worse.

311
00:13:19,089 --> 00:13:20,879
Fat Tony told me to lose the finals.

312
00:13:20,966 --> 00:13:24,006
Not win by a little, but lose... or else.

313
00:13:24,094 --> 00:13:25,264
"Or else"?

314
00:13:25,346 --> 00:13:27,556
My client does not
speak like that.

315
00:13:27,640 --> 00:13:30,680
Yeah, now drop the subject,
or else.

316
00:13:30,768 --> 00:13:33,148
Edit that out, or else.

317
00:13:33,229 --> 00:13:36,149
I-I'm gonna stop talking...
or else.

318
00:13:36,232 --> 00:13:37,192
Damn it.

319
00:13:37,274 --> 00:13:39,994
<i>NARRATOR:</i>
<i>What did Fat Tony say to Bart?</i>

320
00:13:40,069 --> 00:13:43,359
<i>His capo, Johnny Tightlips,</i>
<i>refused to talk.</i>

321
00:13:47,368 --> 00:13:49,828
Anyone here own a black
Lincoln Continental,

322
00:13:49,912 --> 00:13:52,122
license plate,
"Zero to Say"?

323
00:13:52,206 --> 00:13:53,326
It's being towed.

324
00:13:53,415 --> 00:13:54,625
Sir, you're the only one here.

325
00:13:54,708 --> 00:13:55,998
I saw you get out of it.

326
00:13:56,085 --> 00:13:57,545
Yeah, maybe it is.
Maybe I am.

327
00:13:57,628 --> 00:13:59,048
Maybe you did.
Or maybe it's not.

328
00:13:59,129 --> 00:14:00,419
And I'm not, and you didn't.

329
00:14:00,506 --> 00:14:01,876
But you didn't hear this, that,
or the other thing.

330
00:14:01,966 --> 00:14:03,086
Or maybe you did.

331
00:14:03,175 --> 00:14:05,845
Hey! My granny's in there!

332
00:14:05,928 --> 00:14:08,598
Shaving points was one thing,
but he wanted me to lose.

333
00:14:08,681 --> 00:14:11,561
I let down my team.
I let down my town.

334
00:14:20,276 --> 00:14:24,356
So, I guess this is where
I break down and cry.

335
00:14:24,446 --> 00:14:27,906
(crying)

336
00:14:27,992 --> 00:14:30,082
Hey, I'm the one
who's supposed to cry.

337
00:14:30,160 --> 00:14:32,660
No. This is my story.

338
00:14:32,746 --> 00:14:34,416
-Tighten on me.
-Tighten on me.

339
00:14:34,498 --> 00:14:37,208
Fine. Tighten on him
then rack focus to me.

340
00:14:37,293 --> 00:14:40,213
Dad, this is supposed to be
about us getting together.

341
00:14:40,296 --> 00:14:42,376
Fine. Tighten on him.
Rack focus to me.

342
00:14:42,464 --> 00:14:43,554
Cut to a wide shot.

343
00:14:43,632 --> 00:14:44,882
Split screen with Marge.

344
00:14:44,967 --> 00:14:46,387
Truck in, nice and slow.

345
00:14:46,468 --> 00:14:49,218
<i>Then cut to a "B" roll of me</i>
<i>eating a tuna fish sandwich.</i>

346
00:14:49,305 --> 00:14:51,555
Dad, how did you
learn these things?

347
00:14:51,640 --> 00:14:54,140
Son, show business
is everybody's business.

348
00:14:54,226 --> 00:14:56,976
Dutch angle, photo negative
and freeze!

349
00:14:57,062 --> 00:15:00,152
I'm a excommation point!

350
00:15:00,232 --> 00:15:02,822
In the gym that night, you could
cut the tension with a knife,

351
00:15:02,902 --> 00:15:05,402
but, uh, we don't allow
knives in school,

352
00:15:05,487 --> 00:15:06,737
not even in metaphors.

353
00:15:06,822 --> 00:15:09,412
♪ <i>We got to fight</i>
<i>the powers that be</i> ♪

354
00:15:09,491 --> 00:15:10,951
♪ <i>Fight the power</i> ♪

355
00:15:12,328 --> 00:15:13,908
♪ <i>Fight the power</i> ♪

356
00:15:13,996 --> 00:15:16,166
(crowd cheering)

357
00:15:18,542 --> 00:15:20,752
ANGER WATKINS:
Another bucket by Bart Simpson!

358
00:15:20,836 --> 00:15:22,666
His sloppy play
is a distant memory,

359
00:15:22,755 --> 00:15:24,335
like Nelson's father.

360
00:15:24,423 --> 00:15:25,803
Yeah, interesting
side note:

361
00:15:25,883 --> 00:15:28,723
Nelson left a ticket for his
father in case he showed up.

362
00:15:28,802 --> 00:15:31,312
And he did show up,
but then he sold the ticket

363
00:15:31,388 --> 00:15:33,808
without seeing Nelson,
and he skipped town again.

364
00:15:33,891 --> 00:15:35,021
You believe that?

365
00:15:35,100 --> 00:15:37,060
Rejected!

366
00:15:37,144 --> 00:15:38,274
Like I've been rejected.

367
00:15:38,354 --> 00:15:40,274
Nothing but net!

368
00:15:40,356 --> 00:15:42,016
Which is what my mom
wears in the strip club.

369
00:15:42,107 --> 00:15:45,187
{\an8}It was in the third quarter
when the game really got weird,

370
00:15:45,277 --> 00:15:47,487
{\an8}and I got a low bar for weird.

371
00:15:48,280 --> 00:15:49,280
(grunts)

372
00:15:49,365 --> 00:15:51,655
Bart went to shoot,
and took a hard foul

373
00:15:51,742 --> 00:15:53,202
from his own best friend.

374
00:15:53,285 --> 00:15:55,155
♪ ♪

375
00:16:05,714 --> 00:16:10,144
Let's just say Bart wasn't the only one
Fat Tony had gotten to.

376
00:16:10,219 --> 00:16:12,549
This <i>was</i> my bobblehead.

377
00:16:12,638 --> 00:16:16,808
They got to him, in my bedroom,
where he bobbled.

378
00:16:16,892 --> 00:16:18,812
Hey, let's just say
that bobblehead

379
00:16:18,894 --> 00:16:21,484
won't be attending
no more giveaway days.

380
00:16:21,563 --> 00:16:23,403
{\an8}You keep shooting your mouth,

381
00:16:23,482 --> 00:16:26,612
{\an8}you'll wind up in that building
going up on Third Street.

382
00:16:26,694 --> 00:16:29,744
{\an8}It's a Third Street address,
but actually you enter on Lincoln.

383
00:16:29,822 --> 00:16:31,992
{\an8}Yet another secret revealed!

384
00:16:32,074 --> 00:16:34,544
I'm sorry, Dad.
I was a jerk.

385
00:16:34,618 --> 00:16:36,578
The good thing
about being a kid

386
00:16:36,662 --> 00:16:39,832
is you get to make mistakes so
you don't make them as an adult.

387
00:16:39,915 --> 00:16:40,995
Thanks, Dad.

388
00:16:41,083 --> 00:16:42,713
But don't you still
make mistakes?

389
00:16:42,793 --> 00:16:46,173
The best one was you, son. Aw.

390
00:16:46,255 --> 00:16:47,505
Now go win that game!

391
00:16:47,589 --> 00:16:49,969
<i>NARRATOR:</i>
<i>And win he did.</i>

392
00:16:51,677 --> 00:16:54,177
He blew our net budget
for the next ten years.

393
00:16:55,180 --> 00:16:56,640
(buzzer blares)

394
00:16:56,724 --> 00:16:59,064
<i>NARRATOR:</i>
<i>But not everyone was cheering.</i>

395
00:16:59,143 --> 00:17:00,443
Is he going for a gun?

396
00:17:00,519 --> 00:17:01,559
(sighs)
Oh.

397
00:17:01,645 --> 00:17:03,185
-Get me a gun.
-(screams)

398
00:17:03,272 --> 00:17:04,862
We thought we
were goners.

399
00:17:04,940 --> 00:17:07,530
Our lives flashed
before our eyes.

400
00:17:07,609 --> 00:17:09,609
I had a lot of crazy jobs.

401
00:17:09,695 --> 00:17:12,275
And then the cavalry came
on her stupid high horse.

402
00:17:12,364 --> 00:17:13,704
LISA:
Let them go.

403
00:17:13,782 --> 00:17:16,912
Really? And what
do you have on me?

404
00:17:16,994 --> 00:17:17,954
The goods.

405
00:17:18,037 --> 00:17:19,907
The goods?
Oh, that sounds bad.

406
00:17:19,997 --> 00:17:22,617
Fat Tony, may I speak
to you in Italian?

407
00:17:22,708 --> 00:17:24,418
I don't know Italian.

408
00:17:24,501 --> 00:17:25,751
How about Sicilian?

409
00:17:25,836 --> 00:17:26,876
That's a language?

410
00:17:26,962 --> 00:17:28,712
How about I say it
like Porky Pig?

411
00:17:28,797 --> 00:17:30,007
E-ba-dee, e-ba-dee, e-ba-dee,
e-ba-dee, e-ba-dee...

412
00:17:30,090 --> 00:17:31,550
Say what you got to say.

413
00:17:31,633 --> 00:17:34,433
Turns out I'm the hero
of this documentary.

414
00:17:34,511 --> 00:17:36,061
I think that deserves a chyron.

415
00:17:38,015 --> 00:17:40,515
It happens that
Fat Tony had a secret,

416
00:17:40,601 --> 00:17:43,691
a secret I had uncovered
with a little bit of research.

417
00:17:43,771 --> 00:17:46,691
<i>I wondered,</i>
<i>if Fat Tony liked basketball so much,</i>

418
00:17:46,774 --> 00:17:47,944
<i>why didn't he play?</i>

419
00:17:48,025 --> 00:17:49,855
<i>Turns out he had.</i>

420
00:17:49,943 --> 00:17:52,153
<i>For a girls' team.</i>

421
00:17:52,237 --> 00:17:55,237
<i>And if there's one thing</i>
<i>a Mafia boss doesn't want known,</i>

422
00:17:55,324 --> 00:17:57,664
<i>it's that he was</i>
<i>the third-string shooting guard</i>

423
00:17:57,743 --> 00:18:00,123
<i>on the Springfield Little Debbies.</i>

424
00:18:02,122 --> 00:18:04,212
You keep quiet
about what you know.

425
00:18:04,291 --> 00:18:06,001
All of you keep quiet!

426
00:18:06,085 --> 00:18:07,415
Keep quiet about what, boss?

427
00:18:07,503 --> 00:18:08,883
The man-Spanx you wear?

428
00:18:08,962 --> 00:18:11,132
Your high school nickname,
Robert DeZero?

429
00:18:11,215 --> 00:18:13,375
The way you cried
at <i>Toy Story 2?</i>

430
00:18:13,467 --> 00:18:14,927
That's not even the sad one.

431
00:18:15,010 --> 00:18:16,010
What? What?

432
00:18:16,095 --> 00:18:18,215
Why do you keep talking?

433
00:18:18,305 --> 00:18:20,055
I'm sorry.
It's a nervous condition.

434
00:18:20,140 --> 00:18:23,560
Can you give me the name
of that secret shrink you see?

435
00:18:23,644 --> 00:18:24,854
So, we made a deal.

436
00:18:24,937 --> 00:18:27,397
I'd forget if Fat Tony forgave.

437
00:18:27,481 --> 00:18:29,271
But now the secret's out.

438
00:18:29,358 --> 00:18:30,858
It's in a documentary.

439
00:18:30,943 --> 00:18:33,493
No one watches those,
unless it's a documentary

440
00:18:33,570 --> 00:18:36,240
where a rich guy kills people
and no one knows about it.

441
00:18:36,323 --> 00:18:38,243
As far as you know.
(chuckles)

442
00:18:41,662 --> 00:18:43,502
BURNS:
I'm guilty, guilty, guilty.

443
00:18:43,580 --> 00:18:45,080
SMITHERS:
Sir, you know you're on mic.

444
00:18:45,165 --> 00:18:46,875
BURNS: Who is this Mike
you're speaking of?

445
00:18:46,959 --> 00:18:48,169
We'll kill him, too!

446
00:18:48,252 --> 00:18:51,382
<i>NARRATOR: But all sports stories</i>
<i>have an upside,</i>

447
00:18:51,463 --> 00:18:53,803
<i>unless you're</i>
<i>a Detroit Lions fan.</i>

448
00:18:53,882 --> 00:18:57,592
So this young man,
showboat and friend of the mob,

449
00:18:57,678 --> 00:19:00,218
gets off with not even
a slap on the wrist.

450
00:19:00,305 --> 00:19:03,345
It's a travesty
wrapped in outrage,

451
00:19:03,433 --> 00:19:07,193
marinated in a sauce
of everything's gone to hell!

452
00:19:08,647 --> 00:19:10,017
I admit, it was fun.

453
00:19:10,107 --> 00:19:13,277
For a short time,
we had our own little superstar.

454
00:19:13,360 --> 00:19:14,900
And he kept playing.

455
00:19:14,987 --> 00:19:17,317
Then he ran up
against one tall kid,

456
00:19:17,406 --> 00:19:19,576
<i>and found out</i>
<i>he really wasn't that good.</i>

457
00:19:19,658 --> 00:19:23,578
But Lisa, Lisa had a real
talent for journalism.

458
00:19:23,662 --> 00:19:25,122
Whatever that gets us.

459
00:19:25,205 --> 00:19:27,785
Homer, we have to end
on something sweet.

460
00:19:27,875 --> 00:19:30,495
(lovingly)
Whatever that gets us.

461
00:19:33,589 --> 00:19:36,469
{\an8}-♪ <i>Now basketball is my favorite sport</i> ♪
-♪ <i>Uh-huh</i> ♪

462
00:19:36,550 --> 00:19:37,930
{\an8}♪ <i>I like the way they dribble</i>
<i>up and down the court</i> ♪

463
00:19:38,010 --> 00:19:38,930
{\an8}<i>-♪ Come On ♪</i>
-(whistle blows)

464
00:19:39,011 --> 00:19:40,851
{\an8}♪ <i>I keep it so fresh</i>
<i>on the microphone</i> ♪

465
00:19:40,929 --> 00:19:42,179
{\an8}♪ <i>I like no interruption</i>
<i>when the game is on</i> ♪

466
00:19:42,264 --> 00:19:43,354
{\an8}♪ <i>Game's on</i> ♪

467
